<div id="p402" class="blockpost rowodd firstpost">
	<h2><span><span class="conr">#1&nbsp;</span><a href="viewtopic.php?pid=402#p402">2008-08-29 04:00:24</a></span></h2>
	<div class="box">
		<div class="inbox">
			<div class="postleft">
				<dl>
					<dt><strong><a href="profile.php?id=89993">laZee</a></strong></dt>
					<dd class="usertitle"><strong>Member</strong></dd>
					<dd class="postavatar"></dd>
				</dl>
			</div>
			<div class="postright">
				<h3>Peer download progress monitoring?</h3>
				<div class="postmsg">
					<p>Hey there,<br /><br />we are setting up a bittorrent tracker for deploying patches on multiple machines. The machine where the tracker is located should be able to monitor the progress of the download for each peer.<br /><br />A tracker-request contains a parameter called &quot;left&quot; which has the information of the amount of bytes left to download. So this would be nice to use for checking which peer completed the download.<br /><br />I tried OpenTracker as Tracker-Software, but i see no possibility to get the information of the &quot;left&quot; bytes for each peer. Is this possible? For what is the &quot;left&quot; parameter used in the protocol? Does anybody have an idea, how one could monitor the download progress from the tracker machine?<br /><br />Thanks in advance,<br />laZee</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="clearer"></div>
			<div class="postfootleft"><p>Offline</p></div>
			<div class="postfootright"><div>&nbsp;</div></div>
		</div>
